  "body": "Our cluster is easy to take down and it's also a single point of failure; service stops if it's attacked.\n\nMore context:\n\n> Cluster is small and can be taken down, the ultimate solution is to get our changes upstream and Whisper enabled by default (but we should prove that Whisper is indeed scalable, and if not, make it so which requires protocol work) \n> \n> In the shorter term, we can decentralize our specialized nodes by putting Status nodes on DAppNode.io it's very easy all we need to do is provide a Docker Image (which we already have) \n> \n> We can also enable our mail servers for Status Desktop, which was the original idea. (and later users can earn SNT for delivering mailserver requests)\n> \n> From Jordi about Dappnode\n> You can connect @eduadiez:matrix.org via Riot Check https://dappnode.io\n> \n> In addition to this we can introduce a simple Staking model where to fulfil service a user should stake SNT on a trust-basis, where the cluster node can claim the SNT whenever it desires (the \"gentleman's agreement\" being that the node won't touch the stake except when it beleives there is bad behaviour.\n> \n> This can also be extended for public chats, although will require user-client quorum.\n\n",
